section_name: internal taxes collected at the border
text: ['3.1.5  Internal taxes and other charges collected at the border']

section_name: internal taxes collected at the border
text: ['3.1.5  Internal taxes collected at the border', '3.39.  Saudi Arabia does not have a value added tax (VAT) or excise duties, therefore no internal taxes on imported goods are collected at the border.', '3.40.  There  is  an  "other  duty  or  charge"  (ODC)  imposed  on  tobacco  and  tobacco  products  at SAR 0.03 for each packet, as set out in Schedule CLVIII of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, which, the authorities stated, is applied for public health reasons.', "3.41.  For  goods  left  in  Customs  Department's  sheds  and  not  cleared  within  10  days  of  the unloading date, storage charges are levied at SAR 20 per tonne per day; no charges are levied if the delay was not caused by the importer. Goods in transit are subject to a service charge at a rate of 0.004% of the customs value. The authorities indicated that the charge is commensurate with the service cost.", '3.42.  There are no customs inspection charges imposed on goods. However, a scanning charge of SAR 100 per consignment is applied to scanned goods.']
